{
  "texts": [
    "The approach improves diagnostic accuracy by integrating multiple modalities, outperforming individual ones.",
    "[9] The international collaborations, especially between developed countries like the USA, China, and the UK, have been crucial in accelerating research, allowing for larger datasets, broader clinical trials, and more robust validation processes, ultimately pushing the field toward more impactful innovations.",
    "Despite this progress, deep learning (DL) and transfer learning (TL) techniques have yet to be established as primary clinical protocols for breast cancer detection and patient survivability assessment.",
    "Thus, global collaboration within the scientific community is essential to undertake the necessary medical device regulations for the integration of deep learning technology in healthcare.",
    "Consequently, this systematic bibliometric review serves as a valuable resource for novices aiming to apply Deep Learning and Transfer Learning techniques for breast cancer diagnosis and treatment using various medical imaging modalities."
  ]
}